#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:0.5"
msgid "56. Jotikasikkhāpada"
msgstr ""
"<hgroup><h1 id=\"Bu-Pc.56\">Monks’ Confession 56: the training rule on "
"fire</h1></hgroup>"

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
#. VAR: susumāragire → suṃsumāragire (bj, s1, s2, pts1) | saṃsumāragire (mr)
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena samayena buddho bhagavā bhaggesu viharati susumāragire bhesakaḷāvane "
"migadāye."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"nidana\">Origin story</h2>\n"
"<h3 id=\"anunidana1\">First sub-story</h3>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.56.1\"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-"
"Pc.56.1.1\">Bu-Pc.56.1.1</a><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.398\""
">BD.2.398</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1067</a>At one time the Buddha was staying "
"in the Bhagga country at Susumāragira in the Bhesakaḷā Grove, the deer park."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.2"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū hemantike kāle aññataraṃ mahantaṃ "
"susirakaṭṭhaṃ jotiṃ samādahitvā visibbesuṃ."
msgstr ""
"On one occason during winter the monks were warming themselves after setting "
"fire to a hollow log."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.3"
msgid ""
"Tasmiñca susire kaṇhasappo agginā santatto nikkhamitvā bhikkhū paripātesi."
msgstr ""
"Being heated by the fire, a black snake came out of the log and attacked the "
"monks."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.4"
msgid "Bhikkhū tahaṃ tahaṃ upadhāviṃsu."
msgstr "The monks ran here and there.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.5"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1068</a>The monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.6"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized them,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.7"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma bhikkhū jotiṃ samādahitvā visibbessantī”ti … pe …"
msgstr "“How can those monks light a fire to warm themselves?” …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.8"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira, bhikkhave, bhikkhū jotiṃ samādahitvā visibbentī”ti?"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that some monks did this?”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.9"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.10"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha criticized them, “…"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.11"
msgid ""
"kathañhi nāma te, bhikkhave, moghapurisā jotiṃ samādahitvā visibbessanti."
msgstr "How can those foolish men light a fire to warm themselves?"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.12"
msgid "Netaṃ, bhikkhave, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.13"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc3
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.14"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu visibbanāpekkho jotiṃ samādaheyya vā samādahāpeyya vā, "
"pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h3 id=\"anupannatti1\">First preliminary ruling</h3>\n"
"<p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1069</a>‘If a monk lights a fire to "
"warm himself, or gets one lit, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.1.15"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"<p class=\"endsection\"><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.399\">BD.2.399</a><"
"a class=\"wt-pa\">1070</a>In this way the Master laid down this training "
"rule for the monks.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.2.1"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū gilānā honti."
msgstr ""
"<h3 id=\"anunidana2\">Second sub-story</h3>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.56.1.2\">Bu-Pc.56.1.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1071</a>At one time a number of monks were sick."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.2.2"
msgid "Gilānapucchakā bhikkhū gilāne bhikkhū etadavocuṃ—"
msgstr "The monks who were looking after them asked,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.2.3"
msgid "“kaccāvuso, khamanīyaṃ, kacci yāpanīyan”ti?"
msgstr "“We hope you’re bearing up; we hope you’re getting better?”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.2.4"
msgid "“Pubbe mayaṃ, āvuso, jotiṃ samādahitvā visibbema;"
msgstr "<p>“Previously we lit a fire to warm ourselves,"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.2.5"
msgid "tena no phāsu hoti."
msgstr "and then we were comfortable."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.2.6"
msgid ""
"Idāni pana ‘bhagavatā paṭikkhittan’ti kukkuccāyantā na visibbema, tena no na "
"phāsu hotī”ti."
msgstr ""
"But now that this has been prohibited by the Master, we don’t warm ourselves "
"because we’re afraid of wrongdoing. Because of that we’re not "
"comfortable.”</p>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.2.7"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "<p>They told the Master. …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.2.8"
msgid ""
"anujānāmi, bhikkhave, gilānena bhikkhunā jotiṃ samādahitvā vā samādahāpetvā "
"vā visibbetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“<strong class=\"rule\">Monks, I allow a sick monk to light a fire to warm "
"himself, or to get one lit.</strong>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.2.9"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc6, pts-vp-pli4.116
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.2.10"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu agilāno visibbanāpekkho jotiṃ samādaheyya vā samādahāpeyya "
"vā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h3 id=\"anupannatti2\">Second preliminary ruling</h3>\n"
"<p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1072</a>‘If a monk who is not sick "
"lights a fire to warm himself, <a class=\"pts-vp-pi\" id=\"Vin.4.116\""
">Vin.4.116</a> or gets one lit, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:1.2.11"
msgid "Evañcidaṃ bhagavatā bhikkhūnaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ paññattaṃ hoti."
msgstr ""
"<p class=\"endsection\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1073</a>In this way the Master "
"laid down this training rule for the monks.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc8
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:2.1.1"
msgid ""
"Tena kho pana samayena bhikkhū padīpepi jotikepi jantāgharepi kukkuccāyanti."
msgstr ""
"<h3 id=\"anunidana3\">Third sub-story</h3>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.56.2\">Bu-Pc.56.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1074</a>Soon afterwards the monks did not light lamps, small fires, or "
"saunas because they were afraid of wrongdoing."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:2.1.2"
msgid "Bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "They told the Master …"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:2.1.3"
msgid ""
"anujānāmi, bhikkhave, tathārūpappaccayā jotiṃ samādahituṃ samādahāpetuṃ."
msgstr ""
"“<strong class=\"rule\">Monks, I allow you to light a fire, or to get one "
"lit, if there’s a suitable reason.</strong>"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:2.1.4"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And so, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="rule">
#. REF: sc9
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:2.1.5"
msgid ""
"“Yo pana bhikkhu agilāno visibbanāpekkho jotiṃ samādaheyya vā samādahāpeyya "
"vā, aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pannatti\">Final ruling</h2>\n"
"<p class=\"rule\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1075</a>‘If a monk who is not sick "
"lights a fire to warm himself, or gets one lit, unless there is an "
"appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession.’”</p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc10
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.1"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"pada\">Definitions</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.56.3\"></a><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-"
"Pc.56.3.1\">Bu-Pc.56.3.1</a><a class=\"wt-pa\">1076</a><term>A</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.2"
msgid "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "<gloss>whoever …</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b><b class="term">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.3"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "<term>Monk</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.4"
msgid "… pe …"
msgstr ""
"<gloss>…The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order "
"through a procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is "
"unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.5"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc11
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.6"
msgid "Agilāno nāma"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"pts-vp-en\" id=\"BD.2.400\">BD.2.400</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1077</a><term>Who is not sick</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.7"
msgid "yassa vinā agginā phāsu hoti."
msgstr "<gloss>he is comfortable without a fire.</gloss>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc12
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.8"
msgid "Gilāno nāma"
msgstr "<a class=\"wt-pa\">1078</a><term>Who is sick</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.9"
msgid "yassa vinā agginā na phāsu hoti."
msgstr "<gloss>he is not comfortable without a fire.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc13
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.10"
msgid "Visibbanāpekkhoti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1079</a><term>To warm himself</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.11"
msgid "tappitukāmo."
msgstr "<gloss>wanting to heat himself.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc14
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.12"
msgid "Joti nāma"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1080</a><term>A fire</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.13"
msgid "aggi vuccati."
msgstr "<gloss>flames are what is meant.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc15
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.14"
msgid "Samādaheyyāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1081</a><term>Lights</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.15"
msgid "sayaṃ samādahati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"<gloss>if he lights it himself, he commits an offense entailing "
"confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc16
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.16"
msgid "Samādahāpeyyāti"
msgstr "<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1082</a><term>Gets one lit</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.17"
msgid "aññaṃ āṇāpeti, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr "<gloss>if he asks another, he commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </b>
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.18"
msgid "Sakiṃ āṇatto bahukampi samādahati, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he only asks once, then even if the other lights many fires, he commits "
"one offense entailing confession.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </p><p><b class="term">
#. REF: sc17
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.19"
msgid "Aññatra tathā rūpappaccayāti"
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1083</a><term>Unless there is a appropriate "
"reason</term>:"

#. HTML: </b><b class="gloss">
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.1.20"
msgid "ṭhapetvā tathārūpappaccayaṃ."
msgstr "<gloss>except if there is an appropriate reason.</gloss></p>"

#. HTML: </b></p><p>
#. REF: sc18
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.2.1"
msgid ""
"Agilāno agilānasaññī visibbanāpekkho jotiṃ samādahati vā samādahāpeti vā, "
"aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"h2 id=\"cakka\">Permutations</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.56.3.2\">Bu-Pc.56.3.2</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1084</a>If he is not sick, and he does not perceive himself as sick, and he "
"lights a fire to warm himself, or gets one lit, unless there is an "
"appropriate reason, he commits an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.2.2"
msgid ""
"Agilāno vematiko visibbanāpekkho jotiṃ samādahati vā samādahāpeti vā, "
"aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is not sick, but he is unsure of it, and he lights a fire to warm "
"himself, or gets one lit, unless there is an appropriate reason, he commits "
"an offense entailing confession."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.2.3"
msgid ""
"Agilāno gilānasaññī visibbanāpekkho jotiṃ samādahati vā samādahāpeti vā, "
"aññatra tathārūpappaccayā, āpatti pācittiyassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is not sick, but he perceives himself as sick, and he lights a fire to "
"warm himself, or gets one lit, unless there is an appropriate reason, he "
"commits an offense entailing confession."

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc19
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.2.4"
msgid "Paṭilātaṃ ukkhipati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"<p><a class=\"wt-pa\">1085</a>If he puts back a burning piece of wood that "
"has fallen off, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.2.5"
msgid "Gilāno agilānasaññī, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is sick, but he does not perceive himself as sick, he commits an "
"offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.2.6"
msgid "Gilāno vematiko, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr ""
"If he is sick, but he is unsure if he is, he commits an offense of wrong "
"conduct."

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.2.7"
msgid "Gilāno gilānasaññī, anāpatti."
msgstr ""
"If he is sick, and he perceives himself as sick, there is no offense.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc20
#, fuzzy
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.3.1"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr ""
"<h2 id=\"anapatti\">Non-offenses</h2>\n"
"<p><a class=\"pts-cs\" id=\"Bu-Pc.56.3.3\">Bu-Pc.56.3.3</a><a class=\"wt-pa\""
">1086</a>There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.3.2"
msgid ""
"gilānassa, aññena kataṃ visibbeti, vītaccitaṅgāraṃ visibbeti, padīpe jotike "
"jantāghare tathārūpappaccayā, āpadāsu, ummattakassa, ādikammikassāti."
msgstr ""
"if he is sick; if he warms himself over a fire lit by another; if he warms "
"himself over flameless coals; if he lights a lamp, a small fire, or a sauna, "
"when there is an appropriate reason; if there are dangers; if he is insane; "
"if he is the first offender.</p>"

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsutta">
#. REF: sc21
msgctxt "pli-tv-bu-vb-pc56:3.3.3"
msgid "Jotikasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ chaṭṭhaṃ."
msgstr ""
"<p class=\"endsutta\"><a class=\"wt-pa\">1087</a>The sixth rule, the "
"training rule on fire, is finished.</p>"
